        <div id= "respite-care-services"class="things-to-know">
          <h2>RESPITE CARE SERVICES</h2>
          <br>
          <br>
          <p>
            Family caregivers put long hours into caring for their relatives which can take a toll on their personal lives and their health.  Our respite care services will allow your family caregivers to take some time off while our licensed caregivers provide care for you or your loved ones.
          <br>
            The responsibilities of being a family caregiver can be difficult to handle as family caregivers end up devoting much of their time to providing home care.  This makes it difficult to have a career or spend time with immediate family.  The long hours of being a family caregiver can also be stressful and cause the caregiver to lose sleep which can lead to physical health problems and other issues such as depression.
            <br>
            Our respite care services can benefit your family caregiver and you or your loved one receiving the care by allowing the family caregiver some time off to recharge and deal with personal matters.  While the family caregiver takes time off, you or your loved ones will be in the hands of our trained and licensed caregiver.
            <br>
            When you call us for respite care services, we will evaluate the care needs of you or your loved ones as well as the type of care that the family caregiver provides.  Living Spring Home Care Services will make sure that our caregiver provides the type of care that you or your loved one is used to from the family caregiver to make the transition as seamless as possible.
            <br>
            <strong>Our respite care services provide the following:</strong>
            <br>
            <br>
            <ul class="wwd-list">
              <li>Quality care from our licensed caregivers</li>
              <li>Care similar to that provided by the family caregiver</li>
              <li>Scheduled time off for the family caregiver</li>
  
            </ul>  
          </p>
          <br>

          </div>
        <div id= "hospice-care-services"class="things-to-know">
          <h2>HOSPICE CARE SERVICES </h2>
          <br>
          <br>
          <p>
            Our caregivers will provide care to help keep those affected comfortable and pain free so they can live their final days with peace and dignity.
          <br>
            Hospice care is the care that people receive when they have a limited life expectancy or a terminal illness.  The purpose of hospice care is to keep the care recipient as comfortable and pain free as possible and allow them to live their remaining days with dignity.
            <br>
            At Living Spring Home Care Services, our caregivers provide personal care and companionship for senior citizens to ensure that they get excellent care and meaningful companionship.  Our caregivers aim to provide more than just quality care for you or your loved ones.  We will get to know you or your loved ones on a personal level to be a friend to them and provide them with good company.
            <br>
            Our caregivers can provide your loved ones with hospice care which will allow your family to manage other affairs and visit with your loved ones.  Our care manager will help develop a personalized care plan based on your loved one’s unique needs to help keep them comfortable and pain free.  
            <br>
            Our hospice care services start with an in-home assessment so that we can understand the specific care needs of your loved one.  We will then form a care plan that includes non-medical assistance to address their needs and ensure they are comfortable in their final days.
          </p>
          <br>

          </div>
        <div id= "fall-prevention-services"class="things-to-know">
          <h2>FALL PREVENTION SERVICES</h2>
          <br>
          <br>
          <p>
            Per the CDC, most severe injuries and deaths for elderly adults older than 65 years old are caused by falls as a result of medications, illnesses, and environmental factors.
          <br>
            Their data also states that seniors are 75 percent more likely to suffer another fall within six months.
            <br>
            A neat, tidy, organized home environment, can greatly reduce the risk of falls while a crowded, messy living space, leads to a heightened risk. Less allergens can also relieve chronic allergies and respiratory issues, but cleaning can be a tough task for some seniors.
            <br>
            Our friendly, well-trained caregivers know the causes and risks of falling. We can help with the following:
            <br>
            <br>
            <ul class="wwd-list">
              <li>Getting up and out of bed and from chairs</li>
              <li>Preparing meals</li>
              <li>Cleaning the home</li>
              <li>Physical therapy exercises</li>
              <li>Engaging in conversations </li>
              <li>Participating in mental stimulation games</li>
              <li>Providing medication reminders</li>
            </ul>  
          </p>
          <br>

          </div>
