        <div id= "post-surgical-care-services"class="things-to-know">
          <h2> POST-SURGICAL CARE</h2>
          <br>
          <br>
          <p>
            Our caregivers will care for individuals after surgery and help them follow their doctor’s orders to ensure they fully recover from their surgery.
            <br>
            Numerous healthcare changes over the past few years have resulted in a lot of patients getting discharged from rehabilitation centers following surgery or an illness before they’re able to provide their own care. 
            <br>
            In such a case, families need to search for other options. Many patients don’t want to go to a nursing home or other post-operative care facility. Rather, they prefer the comfort and familiarity of their own home, but it’s unsafe for them to be there on their own.
            <br>
            At Living Spring Home Care Services, we offer post-surgical care services to help you or your loved ones recover at their home. Abiding to all doctors’ instructions and post-operative care procedures is crucial in order to ensure a complete recovery. Our caregivers are aware of this and will make sure your loved one follows the doctor’s instructions to make a full recovery.
            <br>
            We will develop a personalized home care plan for you or your loved one by speaking with their nurses, surgical coordinators, and/or doctors. Furthermore, our caregivers are all properly trained to help patients with the transition process. With our services, we strive to provide your loved one with a safe and seamless transition back home so they can fully recover.
          </p>
          <br>

          </div>
        <div id= "alzheimer-demential-memory-care-services"class="things-to-know">
          <h2> ALZHEIMER’S, DEMENTIA AND MEMORY CARE SERVICES</h2>
          <br>
          <br>
          <p>
            Those suffering from Alzheimer’s, Parkinson’s disease, and other forms of dementia benefit from receiving care in their own homes.  However, those suffering from these conditions need consistent care to manage their symptoms and keep them safe which is difficult for families to provide.  We can provide effective memory care services that will help your loved ones with dementia live safely at home.
            Our caregivers at Living Spring Home Care Services have the specialized training to care for those with Alzheimer’s and dementia throughout the progression of the disease. Our caregivers can respond to agitation and mood swings with positive reinforcement and we will engage your loved ones in mentally stimulating exercises to help reduce memory loss.
            <br>
            <strong>Our Alzheimer’s and Dementia care services provide the following:</strong>
            <br>
            <br>
            <ul class="wwd-list">
              <li><strong>Companionship: </strong> It is important for those suffering from these conditions to be surrounded by familiar, friendly faces. Our caregivers will build a personal relationship with your loved ones and get to know them through friendly conversation.  We will also engage them in their favorite hobbies and activities which can stabilize their mood and reduce memory loss.</li>
              <li><strong>Personal Care: </strong>  Our caregivers can help keep the home clean by helping with light housekeeping duties. We will take care of household chores including laundry, vacuuming, dusting and emptying the trash.</li>
              <li><strong>Meal Preparation:</strong> Eating regular, nutritious meals is important for the health and well-being of seniors. However, many seniors cannot prepare meals themselves.  Our caregivers will prepare meals for you or your loved ones each day that follow their dietary restrictions and we will even help with the grocery shopping.</li>
              <li><strong>Wandering: </strong> Those who wander around may put themselves in danger, especially if they manage to leave the home. Our caregivers will help your loved ones and ensure that they move around safely and stay in the home.</li>
              <li><strong>Medication Reminders: </strong> We will make sure your loved ones never miss a dose by ensuring they take their medication at the right time.</li>
              <li><strong>Meal Preparation: </strong>Our caregivers will prepare meals daily for your loved ones to make sure they are getting enough nutrition. We will prepare meals in accordance with their dietary restrictions. </li>
            </ul>  
            <p>When you call Living Spring Home Care Services, we will meet with you and your loved ones in their home for an in-home consultation.  During this consultation, we will evaluate the care needs of your loved one and help create an effective care plan.  We will update you if there are any changes in your loved one’s condition and our care plan can be adjusted as the disease progresses.</p> 
            <br>
          </p>

